The South African Weather Service has forecast more heavy downpour in different parts of the country on Sunday. On Saturday night, heavy rain wreaked havoc in may provinces including Gauteng causing flooding. A roof of a popular Pretoria night club collapsed injuring a number of patrons. Forecaster Tokelo Chiloane says, “Today we are expecting more rain especially in parts of Free State, North West and Gauteng. We are also seeing that Mpumalanga and Limpopo will also be getting something. Today, we will be getting more.” SA Weather | Sunday 01 November 2020